Package com.vmware.vapi.bindings.client

Class InvocationConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vapi.bindings.client.InvocationConfig
  • public final class InvocationConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Configuration for a method invocation. If it contains a non-null security context, it would override the security context from the stub configuration.

    • Constructor Summary

      • withReadTimeout

        public static InvocationConfig withReadTimeout​(int readTimeout)
        Static factory for instances with configured timeout as described in ExecutionContext.Builder.setReadTimeout(java.lang.Integer) for one or more specific invocations.

        Usage:
        stub.operation(operationParam, InvocationConfig.readTimeout(1000));

        Parameters:
        readTimeout - non-negative; a value of zero is interpreted as an infinite timeout
        Returns:
        a new instance configured with the specified read-timeout
        See Also:
        ExecutionContext.Builder

        public static InvocationConfig withResponseAccessor​(HttpResponseAccessor accessor)
        Static factory for instances configured with HttpResponseAccessor.
        Parameters:
        accessor - which will be provided with the raw REST response
        Returns:
        a new instance, configured with the specified accessor
        See Also:
        ExecutionContext.Builder
